to read from `entire/checkpoints/v1`\\n   - Gets transcript content and session ID\\n   - Resolves transcript path via agent, writes via `agent.WriteSession()`\\n\\n2. **`restoreSessionTranscriptFromShadow()`** (line 696) - For uncommitted checkpoints (40-char hash ID):\\n   - Opens repo, parses commit hash\\n   - Calls `store.GetTranscriptFromCommit()` which reads from the shadow branch commit tree\\n   - `GetTranscriptFromCommit()` (temporary.go line 575) handles both chunked and non-chunked transcripts\\n   - Falls back through `full.jsonl` then legacy file paths\\n   - Writes via `agent.WriteSession()`\\n\\n3. **`restoreSessionTranscript()`** (line 640) - Local file fallback:\\n   - Copies transcript file directly from the metadata directory\\n\\n### 9. Logs-Only Rewind: `RestoreLogsOnly()`\\n\\n**File:** `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/fix-squash-merge-rewind/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_rewind.go` (line 583)\\n\\nFor committed checkpoints (already condensed to `entire/checkpoints/v1`):\\n1. Reads `CheckpointSummary` from the store\\n2. Optionally checks for newer local logs and prompts for confirmation\\n3. Iterates all sessions in the checkpoint (supports multi-session)\\n4. For each session: reads content, resolves agent, computes transcript path, writes transcript\\n5. Returns `[]RestoredSession` so callers can print per-session resume commands\\n\\n### 10. Session State\\n\\n**File:** `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/fix-squash-merge-rewind/cmd/entire/cli/session/state.go`\\n\\nSession state is stored in `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json`. Key fields for rewind:\\n- `SessionID` - Unique session identifier\\n- `BaseCommit` - Current shadow branch base (HEAD when session started)\\n- `WorktreeID` - Git worktree identifier for branch naming\\n- `UntrackedFilesAtStart` - Files to preserve during rewind\\n- `StepCount` - Number of checkpoints created\\n- `Phase` - Session lifecycle stage (ACTIVE, IDLE, ENDED)\\n- `AgentType` - Agent that created the session\\n\\nThe `StateStore` manages CRUD operations with atomic writes (temp file + rename) and automatic cleanup of stale sessions (7-day threshold).\\n\\n### 10. Integration Tests\\n\\n**File:** `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/fix-squash-merge-rewind/cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/rewind_test.go`\\n\\nTests covering the rewind flow:\\n\\n- **`TestRewind_FullWorkflow`** - 3 checkpoints, rewinds to first, verifies file content and transcript availability\\n- **`TestTaskCheckpoint_RewindWorkflow`** - Task checkpoints via PostToolUse hooks, rewind to task checkpoint, verify file state and truncated transcript\\n- **`TestRewind_MultipleNewFiles`** - Multi-file, multi-directory checkpoints, verifies all files restored correctly\\n- **`TestRewind_MultipleConsecutive`** - Sequential rewinds (v3 -> v2 -> v1), verifies fresh points after each rewind\\n\\n**File:** `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/fix-squash-merge-rewind/cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/logs_only_rewind_test.go`\\n\\nTests for logs-only (committed checkpoint) rewind:\\n\\n- **`TestLogsOnlyRewind_AppearsInRewindList`** - Verifies commits with `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer appear as `IsLogsOnly=true`\\n- **`TestLogsOnlyRewind_RestoresTranscript`** - Verifies transcript is written to agent session directory\\n- **`TestLogsOnlyRewind_DoesNotModifyWorkingDirectory`** - Confirms logs-only does NOT change files or HEAD\\n- **`TestLogsOnlyRewind_DeduplicationWithCheckpoints`** - Same commit not shown as both checkpoint AND logs-only\\n- **`TestLogsOnlyRewind_MultipleCommits`** - Multiple committed sessions all appear\\n- **`TestLogsOnlyRewind_Reset`** - `--reset` performs `git reset --hard`\\n- **`TestLogsOnlyRewind_ResetRestoresTranscript`** - Reset also restores transcript\\n\\n### Summary of the Complete Flow\\n\\n```\\nUser runs: entire rewind\\n  |\\n  v\\nCanRewind() -- always true for manual-commit, generates warning with diff stats\\n  |\\n  v\\nGetRewindPoints(limit=20)\\n  |-- findSessionsForCommit(HEAD) -> reads .git/entire-sessions/*.json\\n  |-- For each session: ListTemporaryCheckpoints(baseCommit, worktreeID, sessionID)\\n  |     -> walks shadow branch commits, parses trailers\\n  |-- GetLogsOnlyRewindPoints()\\n  |     -> reads entire/checkpoints/v1 metadata, scans branch for Entire-Checkpoint trailers\\n  |-- Merge, deduplicate, sort by date\\n  |\\n  v\\nInteractive selection (huh form)\\n  |\\n  v\\n[If IsLogsOnly] -> handleLogsOnlyRewindInteractive() -> sub-menu:\\n  |   logs-only | checkout | reset | cancel\\n  |\\n[If regular checkpoint]:\\n  PreviewRewind() -> warns about files to delete\\n  |\\n  v\\nRewind(point)\\n  |-- resetShadowBranchToCheckpoint() -> moves branch pointer back\\n  |-- Build checkpoint file set from commit tree\\n  |-- Build HEAD tracked file set\\n  |-- Delete untracked files not in checkpoint (respecting preservedUntrackedFiles)\\n  |-- Restore all files from checkpoint tree -> os.WriteFile()\\n  |\\n  v\\nTranscript restoration (3 methods, in order):\\n  1. restoreSessionTranscriptFromStrategy() -- committed checkpoints\\n  2. restoreSessionTranscriptFromShadow()   -- shadow branch (40-char hash)\\n  3. restoreSessionTranscript()             -- local file fallback\\n  |\\n  v\\nPrint: \\\"Rewound to <hash>. claude -r <sessionID>\\\"\\n```\"}],\"totalDurationMs\":1960761,\"totalTokens\":117942,\"totalToolUseCount\":39,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":9454,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":104498,\"output_tokens\":3989,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":9454,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"6c6ebee7-38ae-447f-a418-a164021175d8\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"fbdef524-77e7-412a-a83d-99b37d713b3c\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/fix-squash-merge-rewind\",\"sessionId\":\"6b2dfa34-a5e6-4764-93a3-6738274c6c9a\",\"version\":\"2.1.68\",\"gitBranch\":\"fix/squash-merge-rewind\",\"slug\":\"indexed-swimming-puffin\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_014vJthYRHLVaDKC4Z8UA7Ch\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"## `entire rewind` — Full Explanation\\n\\n### What It Does (User Perspective)\\n\\n**Rewind** lets you roll back your working directory to a previous checkpoint — a snapshot the CLI silently saved while an AI agent was working. Think of it as \\\"undo\\\" for agent sessions.\\n\\n**Why you'd use it:** An agent made changes you don't like, went down a wrong path, or broke something. Instead of manually reverting files, you pick a checkpoint and the CLI restores everything to that exact state.\\n\\n### What the User Sees\\n\\n```\\n$ entire rewind\\n```\\n\\nAn interactive TUI appears listing checkpoints (newest first):\\n\\n```\\n? Select a rewind point:\\n  > [2m ago] Session checkpoint #3 — \\\"Add login feature\\\"\\n    [5m ago] Session checkpoint #2 — \\\"Add login feature\\\"\\n    [8m ago] Session checkpoint #1 — \\\"Add login feature\\\"\\n    [1h ago] Committed: abc123 — \\\"Implement auth system\\\"   (logs only)\\n```\\n\\nEach entry shows the timestamp, a description, and the session prompt that triggered it. **Regular checkpoints** (from the current uncommitted session) restore both files and transcripts. **Logs-only checkpoints** (from already-committed work) only restore the agent transcript so you can resume the conversation — they don't change files.\\n\\nIf you have uncommitted changes, a warning shows the diff stats but doesn't block:\\n\\n```\\n⚠ You have uncommitted changes:\\n  +12 -3  src/auth.go\\n  +5  -0  src/auth_test.go\\nProceed with rewind? [y/N]\\n```\\n\\nAfter confirming, files are restored:\\n\\n```\\nRestored: src/auth.go\\nRestored: src/auth_test.go\\nDeleted:  src/temp_file.go  (wasn't in checkpoint)\\n\\nRewound to abc1234. Resume with: claude -r 2026-03-04-session-uuid\\n```\\n\\n**Non-interactive usage:**\\n\\n```bash\\nentire rewind --list              # JSON list of rewind points\\nentire rewind --to abc1234abc1234 # Direct rewind to specific commit\\nentire rewind --logs-only         # Only restore transcripts\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### How It Works Under the Covers\\n\\n#### Layer 1: Checkpoint Creation (during agent work)\\n\\nEvery time the agent completes a turn, the CLI's hook (`Stop` / `PostToolUse`) calls `SaveStep()`, which:\\n\\n1. Snapshots the entire working directory + metadata into a git tree (in-memory, using go-git plumbing)\\n2. Commits that tree to a **shadow branch** — never touching the user's actual branch\\n3. Updates session state in `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json`\\n\\nThe shadow branch is named `entire/<HEAD-hash[:7]>-<worktreeHash[:6]>` (e.g., `entire/d2fd271-a1b2c3`). Each commit on it is a full snapshot of the repo at that checkpoint.\\n\\n#### Layer 2: Finding Rewind Points\\n\\n`GetRewindPoints()` does two things:\\n\\n**A) Shadow branch checkpoints** (uncommitted sessions):\\n- Reads `.git/entire-sessions/*.json` to find sessions matching the current HEAD\\n- Walks the shadow branch commit log\\n- Parses trailers (`Entire-Session`, `Entire-Metadata`) to associate commits with sessions\\n- Returns these as regular `RewindPoint`s\\n\\n**B) Logs-only checkpoints** (committed work):\\n- Scans the current branch history for commits with `Entire-Checkpoint: <id>` trailers\\n- Looks up the corresponding metadata on `entire/checkpoints/v1` orphan branch\\n- Returns these as `RewindPoint{IsLogsOnly: true}`\\n\\nBoth lists are merged, deduplicated, and sorted newest-first.\\n\\n#### Layer 3: The Actual Rewind\\n\\n`Rewind(point)` does **not** use `git reset` or `git checkout`. It manually restores files:\\n\\n1. **Reset shadow branch pointer** — moves the branch ref to the selected commit (future checkpoints build from here)\\n2. **Build file sets** — reads the checkpoint commit tree and HEAD tree to know what files exist where\\n3. **Delete untracked files** that aren't in the checkpoint and weren't present before the session started (protected by `UntrackedFilesAtStart` in session state)\\n4. **Write every file** from the checkpoint tree to the working directory with `os.WriteFile()`, creating directories as needed\\n5. **Restore the agent transcript** — writes the session transcript (`.jsonl`) to the agent's session directory so the user can resume with `claude -r <session-id>`\\n\\nHEAD and branch pointer are untouched. The user's git history is never modified.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Deep Dive: On-Disk Structures\\n\\n#### 1. Session State Files\\n\\n**Location:** `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json`\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"2026-03-04-a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890\\\",\\n  \\\"base_commit\\\": \\\"d2fd2710abc123def456789012345678abcdef01\\\",\\n  \\\"worktree_id\\\": \\\"a1b2c3\\\",\\n  \\\"step_count\\\": 3,\\n  \\\"phase\\\": \\\"IDLE\\\",\\n  \\\"agent_type\\\": \\\"claude-code\\\",\\n  \\\"untracked_files_at_start\\\": [\\\"notes.txt\\\", \\\"scratch/ideas.md\\\"],\\n  \\\"last_interaction\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T10:30:00Z\\\",\\n  \\\"created_at\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T10:00:00Z\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThese are the lightweight state files that track active sessions. They're used to find which shadow branch to look at.\\n\\n#### 2. Shadow Branch Commits\\n\\n**Branch:** `entire/d2fd271-a1b2c3` (7-char HEAD hash + 6-char worktree hash)\\n\\nEach commit on this branch contains:\\n\\n```\\n<full working directory snapshot>\\n├── src/\\n│   ├── auth.go              # Exact file contents at this checkpoint\\n│   └── auth_test.go\\n├── go.mod\\n├── go.sum\\n└── .entire/metadata/<session-id>/\\n    ├── full.jsonl            # Agent transcript (JSONL format)\\n    ├── prompt.txt            # User prompts for this checkpoint window\\n    └── tasks/<tool-use-id>/  # (if task checkpoint)\\n        ├── checkpoint.json   # {\\\"checkpoint_uuid\\\": \\\"...\\\", \\\"tool_use_id\\\": \\\"...\\\"}\\n        └── agent-<id>.jsonl  # Subagent transcript\\n```\\n\\n**Commit trailers:**\\n```\\nEntire-Session: 2026-03-04-a1b2c3d4-...\\nEntire-Metadata: .entire/metadata/2026-03-04-a1b2c3d4-...\\nEntire-Strategy: manual-commit\\n```\\n\\n#### 3. Condensed Metadata Branch (after user commits)\\n\\n**Branch:** `entire/checkpoints/v1` (orphan branch, never merged)\\n\\nWhen the user makes a git commit, the `post-commit` hook condenses shadow branch data here with a sharded directory layout:\\n\\n```\\n<checkpoint-id[:2]>/<checkpoint-id[2:]>/\\n├── metadata.json\\n├── 0/                        # First session (0-indexed)\\n│   ├── metadata.json         # Session-specific metadata\\n│   ├── full.jsonl            # Transcript\\n│   ├── prompt.txt            # User prompts\\n│   └── content_hash.txt      # SHA256 for dedup\\n├── 1/                        # Second session (if multiple)\\n│   ├── metadata.json\\n│   └── full.jsonl\\n└── ...\\n```\\n\\n**Top-level `metadata.json`:**\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"checkpoint_id\\\": \\\"a3b2c4d5e6f7\\\",\\n  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"2026-03-04-latest-session-uuid\\\",\\n  \\\"session_ids\\\": [\\\"2026-03-04-session-1\\\", \\\"2026-03-04-session-2\\\"],\\n  \\\"session_count\\\": 2,\\n  \\\"strategy\\\": \\\"manual-commit\\\",\\n  \\\"created_at\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T10:35:00Z\\\",\\n  \\\"files_touched\\\": [\\\"src/auth.go\\\", \\\"src/auth_test.go\\\"]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Session-level `metadata.json` (inside `0/`, `1/`, etc.):**\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"2026-03-04-session-1\\\",\\n  \\\"agent\\\": \\\"Claude Code\\\",\\n  \\\"files_touched\\\": [\\\"src/auth.go\\\"],\\n  \\\"created_at\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T10:00:00Z\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThe user's commit on their branch gets an `Entire-Checkpoint: a3b2c4d5e6f7` trailer, creating bidirectional linking between the user's commit and the metadata.\\n\\n#### 4. Transcript Format (`full.jsonl`)\\n\\nEach line is a JSON object representing one interaction turn — the exact format depends on the agent but typically includes role, content, tool calls, and timestamps.\\n\\n#### 5. The `RewindPoint` Struct\\n\\nThe Go struct that ties it all together:\\n\\n```go\\ntype RewindPoint struct {\\n    ID               string          // 40-char commit hash (shadow or user commit)\\n    Message          string          // Human-readable label\\n    MetadataDir      string          // Path within tree (e.g., \\\".entire/metadata/<sid>\\\")\\n    Date             time.Time\\n    IsTaskCheckpoint bool\\n    ToolUseID        string\\n    IsLogsOnly       bool            // true = committed, no file restore\\n    CheckpointID     id.CheckpointID // 12-hex-char ID for logs-only\\n    Agent            types.AgentType\\n    SessionID        string\\n    SessionPrompt    string          // First user prompt (for display)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Flow Summary\\n\\n```\\nAgent works → Stop hook → SaveStep()\\n  → snapshot working dir + metadata → commit to shadow branch\\n  → update .git/entire-sessions/<sid>.json\\n\\nUser runs: entire rewind\\n  → read session states → walk shadow branch → merge with committed checkpoints\\n  → user picks a point\\n  → read commit tree → write files to working dir → restore transcript\\n  → print resume command\\n\\nUser commits → post-commit hook → condense()\\n  → copy metadata from shadow branch to entire/checkpoints/v1\\n  → add Entire-Checkpoint trailer to user's commit\\n  → these become \\\"logs-only\\\" rewind points going forward\\n```\\n\\nThe key design insight: the shadow branch stores **full working directory snapshots** (not diffs), so rewind is a simple tree-read-and-write operation. The user's branch is never touched — no commits, no resets, no history rewriting.\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_t