Squash and Merge\\\" button**: GitHub also concatenates the commit messages (shown as bullet points). All three trailers would appear in the message body.\\n\\n### 4. How the `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer is added (prepare-commit-msg)\\n\\n**File:** `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/fix-squash-merge-rewind/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`, lines 301-478\\n\\nKey behavior at lines 316-323:\\n```go\\nswitch source {\\ncase \\\"merge\\\", \\\"squash\\\":\\n    logging.Debug(logCtx, \\\"prepare-commit-msg: skipped for source\\\",...)\\n    return nil\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThe `prepare-commit-msg` hook **skips entirely** for `source=\\\"merge\\\"` or `source=\\\"squash\\\"`. This means:\\n- When someone runs `git merge --squash feature-branch && git commit`, the prepare-commit-msg hook is called with `source=\\\"\\\"` (normal editor flow), so it **would** add a new trailer if there's an active session\\n- The squash merge commit's message already contains the concatenated messages from the original commits, which include the original trailers\\n\\n### 5. How condensation works in PostCommit\\n\\n**File:** `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/fix-squash-merge-rewind/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`, lines 727-841\\n\\nPostCommit (line 747-748):\\n```go\\ncheckpointID, found := trailers.ParseCheckpoint(commit.Message)\\nif !found {\\n    s.postCommitUpdateBaseCommitOnly(ctx, head)\\n    return nil\\n}\\n```\\n\\nAgain uses `ParseCheckpoint` (singular) -- only the **first** trailer is extracted. The condensation is then performed with this single checkpoint ID.\\n\\n### 6. How `listCheckpoints` matches IDs to metadata\\n\\n**File:** `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/fix-squash-merge-rewind/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go`, lines 35-64\\n\\nThe method calls `store.ListCommitted(ctx)` which reads from the `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch tree. It scans the sharded directory structure (`<id[:2]>/<id[2:]>/`) and reads each checkpoint's metadata. Th