\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_019sZMZKkFnSTUZWxqCAKk1t\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I now have a complete picture of the changes. Here is my review.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Code Review: Fix Squash Merge Rewind\\n\\n### Overall Assessment\\n\\nThis is a clean, well-scoped fix. The implementation correctly addresses the bug where `entire rewind` only parsed the first `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer from squash merge commits, and it achieves consistency with `entire resume` by reusing the same resolution logic. All tests pass. Linting is clean.\\n\\n### What Was Done Well\\n\\n- **Correct root cause fix.** Switching from `ParseCheckpoint` (single match) to `ParseAllCheckpoints` (all matches) in `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/fix-squash-merge-rewind/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_rewind.go` directly addresses the bug.\\n- **Shared helper extraction.** `CollectCheckpointsByAge` in `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/fix-squash-merge-rewind/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go` avoids duplicating the sort-by-creation-time logic between resume and rewind.\\n- **Backward-compatible wrapper.** The local `collectCheckpointsByAge` in `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/fix-squash-merge-rewind/cmd/entire/cli/resume.go` delegates to the new shared helper, keeping the call sites unchanged.\\n- **Thorough integration test.** `REDACTED` in `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/fix-squash-merge-rewind/cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/logs_only_rewind_test.go` covers the full scenario: two sessions, two commits, squash merge, and verification that the latest checkpoint is used.\\n- **Defensive fallback.** `resolveLatestCheckpointFromMap` has a fallback path using the info map's `CreatedAt` when `metadataTree` is nil, which handles edge cases gracefully.\\n\\n### Plan Alignment\\n\\nThe implementation matches the stated requirements precisely:\\n- Multiple `Entire-Checkpoint` trailers are now parsed.\\n- Resolution picks the latest checkpoint by creation time.\\n- Behavior is consistent with `entire resume`.\\n- Shared `CollectCheckpointsByAge` deduplicates logic between resume and rewind.\\n\\n### Issues\\n\\n**Important (should fix):**\\n\\n1. **Double metadata read in the multi-checkpoint path.** In `resolveLatestCheckpointFromMap` at `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/fix-squash-merge-rewind/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_rewind.go` lines 274-283, when there are multiple valid IDs, `CollectCheckpointsByAge` calls `ReadCheckpointMetadata` for each checkpoint ID. However, these same checkpoint IDs already have their metadata loaded in `checkpointInfoMap` (built at lines 155-160 of the same file from `listCheckpoints`). The `CollectCheckpointsByAge` call re-reads metadata from the tree unnecessarily. The fallback path (lines 285-292) already does the right thing -- it uses the in-memory map. For multi-checkpoint squash merges, the fallback logic is sufficient and avoids redundant tree I/O.\\n\\n   Specifically, the `CollectCheckpointsByAge` call reads `CreatedAt` from tree blobs, but `checkpointInfoMap` already contains `CheckpointInfo` structs with `CreatedAt` populated. The fallback loop does the same comparison using `infoMap[cpID].CreatedAt`. Unless the tree metadata and the in-memory metadata could have different `CreatedAt` values (which would be a separate bug), the `CollectCheckpointsByAge` code path is redundant.\\n\\n   Recommendation: Consider removing the `CollectCheckpointsByAge` call from `resolveLatestCheckpointFromMap` and using only the in-memory fallback logic. This simplifies the function and avoids extra tree reads:\\n\\n   ```go\\n   func resolveLatestCheckpointFromMap(cpIDs []id.CheckpointID, infoMap map[id.CheckpointID]CheckpointInfo, _ *object.Tree) (CheckpointInfo, bool) {\\n       var validIDs []id.CheckpointID\\n       for _, cpID := range cpIDs {\\n           if _, ok := infoMap[cpID]; ok {\\n               validIDs = append(validIDs, cpID)\\n           }\\n       }\\n       if len(validIDs) == 0 {\\n           return CheckpointInfo{}, false\\n       }\\n       info := infoMap[validIDs[0]]\\n       for _, cpID := range validIDs[1:] {\\n           if candidate := infoMap[cpID]; candidate.CreatedAt.After(info.CreatedAt) {\\n               info = candidate\\n           }\\n       }\\n       return info, true\\n   }\\n   ```\\n\\n   If there is a reason the tree metadata could differ from the in-memory metadata, that should be documented with a comment.\\n\\n**Suggestions (nice to have):**\\n\\n2. **The `collectCheckpointsByAge` wrapper in resume.go is now trivial.** After the refactoring, the wrapper at `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/fix-squash-merge-rewind/cmd/entire/cli/resume.go` lines 237-241 is a single-line delegation. The comment says it is \\\"kept as a local wrapper for call-site brevity,\\\" but there is only one call site (line 206). Inlining `strategy.CollectCheckpointsByAge(metadataTree, checkpointIDs)` directly would reduce indirection. This is minor and not blocking.\\n\\n3. **Test could verify which checkpoint's transcript is restored.** The test at `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/fix-squash-merge-rewind/cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/logs_only_rewind_test.go` lines 556-575 verifies that *a* transcript `.jsonl` file exists after logs-only rewind, but does not verify that the content corresponds to session 2 (the latest checkpoint). Since the core assertion is that the *latest* checkpoint is chosen, verifying the restored transcript content would strengthen the test. For example, reading the `.jsonl` file and checking it contains \\\"goodbye\\\" rather than \\\"hello\\\" would confirm end-to-end correctness.\\n\\n4. **Type asymmetry between `CollectCheckpointsByAge` and `resolveLatestCheckpointFromMap`.** `CollectCheckpointsByAge` returns `[]*CheckpointInfo` (pointer slice), while `resolveLatestCheckpointFromMap` accepts and returns `CheckpointInfo` (value). At line 279, the code does `la